      "writtenOn": "2026-04-17T00:46:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "bus is just a wrapper created from ipmid_get_sd_bus_connection(), which returns a process-wide shared sd_bus. When the local bus goes out of scope, it does not destroy the underlying D-Bus connection.\nThe match_t objects are effectively tied to that shared global bus, which remains valid for the lifetime of the process. So although it looks like a lifetime issue, it doesn’t lead to a real use-after-free here.",
